{"lemma":"حَسَكِ","slug":"حَسَكِ","root":"ح.س.ك","root_slug":"ح-س-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-س-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7982","n7984","n7985"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"puncture-vine, caltrop (Tribulus terrestris)","examples":[{"text":"(حسك)\n(الماهية) قال ديسقوريدوس الحسك صنفان أحدهما ورقه يشبه ورق بقلة الحمقاء الا أنه أرق منه وله قضبان مستديرة منبسطة على الأرض وعند الورق شوك ملزز صلب وينبت في الخرابات والندى منه وهو ثانيهما ينبت في المواضع الندية والأنهار وقضبانه مرتفعة وورقه أعرض من شوكه حتى أنه يغطيه بعرضه فيخفى وطرف ساقه الاعلى أغلظ من طرفه الأسفل وعليه شئ نابت دقيق في دقة الشعر شبيه بسفا للسنبلة وثمره صلب مثل ثمرة الصنف الآخر وكلا الصنفين يبردان والقوم الذين يكنون بشط نهر سطرموس يعلفون دوابهم بهذا النبات إذا كان رطبا ويعملون من ثمره خبزا لأنه حلو مغذ ويأكلونه وبالجملة البري منهما أرضيته أكثر والبستاني مائيته أكثر إذ هو من جوهر رطب ليست برودته بكثيرة ومن جوهر يابس برودته ليست بيسيرة (الطبع) الحسك صنفاه عند ديسقوريدوس بارد يابس وقال غيره هو حار في أول الأولى يابس فيها وهو أشبه بطبع حسك بلادنا (الافعال والخواص) فيه منع لانصباب المواد لقبضه وانضاج وتليين (الأورام والبثور) يمنع حدوث الأورام الحارة وانصباب المواد وهو جيد لأورام الحلق (الجراح والقروح) ينفع من القروح العفنة واللحم بالعسل (أعضاء الرأس) جيد لقروح اللثة العفنة (أعضاء العين) تنقع عصارته في الاكحال (أعضاء النفس) ينفع من الأورام المطيفة بعضل الحلق (أعضاء النفض) يزيد في الباه ويفتت الحصاة من الكلية والمثانة وكذلك عصارته وينفع من عسر البول والقولنج (السموم) درهمان من ثمره البري لنهش الأفعى ودرهمان منه بالشراب للسموم القاتلة ويرش بطبيخه المكان فيقتل براغيثه.","english":"Canon Medicinae"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thistle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any prickly plant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thorns","tags":["dialectal"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fishbones","tags":["dialectal"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Persian خاشاک (xâšâk), خاشک (xâšak, “chips, leaves, sprigs, shoots, suckers, young grass, small bits of wood, shavings, parings, or refuse of any kind”), from خاش (xâš) of similar meaning suffixed with ـاک (-âk), later also understood as خار (xâr, “thorn”) + شاک (šâk, “twig, shoot”), the خار (xâr, “thorn”) again added in خارخسک (xâr-xasak), خارخشک (xâr-xašak), خارخاسک (xâr-xâsak), خارخاشک (xâr-xâšak), خارخاساک (xâr-xâsâk), خارخاشاک (xâr-xâšâk) meaning Tribulus terrestris."},"ipa":["/ħa.sak/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7982","headword_ar":"حسّك","root":"Hsk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHosiykN","text_ar":"تَحْسِيكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, niggardly, tenacious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avaricious."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, IAth.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7984","headword_ar":"حَسَكٌ","root":"Hsk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is applied, app. in the classical language, as it is in the present day, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Various species of thistle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other prickly plants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"also to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heads of thistles"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caltrop,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribulus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence the explanations here following:] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasak","text_ar":"حَسَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prickly heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the [plant called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodaAn","text_ar":"سَعْدَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Ziyád, Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining to yellowness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Ziyád, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having [a head of] prickles of rounded form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Ziyád, Mgh, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seldom, or never, does any one walk upon it, when it has dried up, without putting upon his feet boots or sandals: and the ants transport its produce"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to their nests:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Ziyád, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant, the produce"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereof (which is rough"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prickly"},{"kind":"text","text":"], TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clings to the wool of sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and to the fur of camels, in their places of pasturing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its leaves are like those of purslane"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ijolap","text_ar":"الرِّجْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or narrower, and at its leaves are compact and hard prickles, having three forks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[hence it seems to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of three-horned caltrop:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or for “ three, ” we should perhaps read"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see another application of the word in what follows:)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the drinking [of an infusion] thereof has the effect of crumbling the stone of the kidneys and bladder; and the drinking of the expressed juice of its leaves is good for the venereal faculty, and for difficulty in the discharge of urine, and for the bite of vipers; and the sprinkling it in the dwelling kills fleas:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) also, accord. to Aboo-Nasr, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produce of the [plant called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafal","text_ar":"نَفَل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp. hard prickles"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thorns:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"msk","text_ar":"مسك"},{"kind":"text","text":":) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh:) which some hold to apply to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any fruit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a plant,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is of the kind termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqodapN","text_ar":"عُقْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forming a compact and roundish head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and hence, to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pod of the cotton-plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a prickle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thorn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasakapN","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is rough."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahumo laHasakN A^amoraAsN","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُمْ لَحَسَكٌ اَمْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily they are strong:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of one person you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marisN","text_ar":"مَرِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasakapN","text_ar":"حَسَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masakapN","text_ar":"مَسَكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa HasakapN","text_ar":"هُوَ حَسَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is courageous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"msk","text_ar":"مسك"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and of a number of persons you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasakN masakN","text_ar":"حَسَكٌ مَسَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in that art., q. v.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasikN","text_ar":"حَسِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasiykapN","text_ar":"حَسِيكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-  Also [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Caltrops,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of instrument used in war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasak","text_ar":"حَسَك"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mentioned in the first sentence of this paragraph,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the prickles of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasak","text_ar":"حَسَك"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of iron,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of canes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around the army,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the ways of the horses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enmity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasakapN","text_ar":"حَسَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasiykapN","text_ar":"حَسِيكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusaAkapN","text_ar":"حُسَاكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K. [The last in the CK written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasAkap","text_ar":"حَساكَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but expressly said in the TA to be with damm, and so written in copies of the S and K.]) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Sadorihi EalaY~a HasiykapN","text_ar":"فِى صَدْرِهِ عَلَىَّ حَسِيكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusaAkapN","text_ar":"حُسَاكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his bosom is rancour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n7985","headword_ar":"حَسِكٌ","root":"Hsk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Affected with rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enmity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"angry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasiku AlS~adori EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسِكُ الصَّدْرِ عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is affected with rancour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bosom against such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasikN marisN","text_ar":"حَسِكٌ مَرِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Courageous [and strong]; not to be attempted [in fight]."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasakN","text_ar":"حَسَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}